text: It's was a random choice, but I glad i make it. This shop was awesome. The sashimi was fresh and delicious with the sauce. The appetizer amaze me with the wonderful combination. They also offer various kinds of sake. The CS was kind and helpful.

All the food was awesome, but the sashimi, potato ball and fried fish were especially delicious. We were with our 9-year-old son and he really enjoyed chicken and rice. The restaurant is a cozy with two tables, which is a great place for families with children to enjoy.

It was a pleasant surprise to discover an authentic and delectable Japanese culinary gem. The chef has an impressive background, having worked in several Michelin-starred restaurants. Every dish we savored was truly delightful. Additionally, Ming provided exceptional service and offered valuable recommendations.
A cute hole in wall shop with cozy atmosphere, generous portions and some memorable dishes. Favourites of the night: the appetiser of the day (beautifully presented!) and pan fried chicken.
Food was amazing, atmosphere was great!! The chef was very friendly and outgoing!! Highly recommend!!! üëçüèª
